  <table class="params">
    <tbody><tr><td class="paramdir">[in]</td><td class="paramname"><code>enable</code></td><td>True to enable the transmitter, false to disable </td></tr>
  </tbody></table>
  </dd>
</dl>

</div>
</div>
<a class="anchor" id="gaaa55a0177d5f0312b515afd1a0fa9bff"></a>
<div class="memitem">
<div class="memproto">
      <table class="memname">
        <tbody><tr>
          <td class="memname">void spi_peripheral_enableReceiver </td>
          <td>(</td>
          <td class="paramtype">bool&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="paramname"><code>enable</code></td><td>)</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody></table>
</div><div class="memdoc">
<p>Enable/disable receiving bytes from the controller into the internal buffer. This function makes it possible to avoid filling up the buffer with 0xFF while a controller is polling for new data.</p>
<dl class="params"><dt>Parameters</dt><dd>
  <table class="params">
    <tbody><tr><td class="paramdir">[in]</td><td class="paramname"><code>enable</code></td><td>True to enable the receiver, false to disable </td></tr>
  </tbody></table>
  </dd>
</dl>

</div>
</div>
<a class="anchor" id="gaf5a027e9a6c8dbd6a1001ffd0143a477"></a>
